<li><span class="plainlinks"><a href="http://patft.uspto.gov/netacgi/nph-Parser?patentnumber=2752158" class="external text" title="http://patft.uspto.gov/netacgi/nph-Parser?patentnumber=2752158" rel="nofollow">U.S. Patent 2,752,158</a></span><span class="PDFlink noprint"><a href="http://www.pat2pdf.org/pat2pdf/foo.pl?number=2752158" class="external text" title="http://www.pat2pdf.org/pat2pdf/foo.pl?number=2752158" rel="nofollow">&#160;</a></span> – "<i>Game apparatus</i>" – This patent used to protect the jagged edges of bonus squares, which were added so that one need not lift previously placed tiles in order to see the bonus. It expired decades ago.</li>
</ul>


